# JOYWORK Frontend UI

- Prefer functional components and add `"use client"` only when hooks, browser APIs, editors, uploads, or client-side interactivity are required.
- Keep new route pages thin; if a page is already large, extract more logic out instead of growing the page further.
- New forms should default to `react-hook-form` + `zodResolver`; keep manual `safeParse` style only when touching a local legacy flow.
- Every form or mutation should model loading, disabled, inline field errors, and `toast.success` or `toast.error` behavior consistently.
- Use React Query for server state and invalidation; keep Zustand reserved for cross-page state like auth, not page-local or form-local state.
- Sanitize rich text or HTML before sending or rendering it, especially around editor output and `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`.
- Reuse existing `src/components/ui` primitives and prefer `src/components/ui/dialog` for new modal work unless a touched legacy feature already uses another dialog stack.
